<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>flexbox | break-after, column, item</title>
<link href="http://opera.com" rel="author" title="Opera Software" />
<link href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css-flexbox-1/#pagination" rel="help" />
<meta content="interact paged" name="flags" />
<style>
* {widows: 1; orphans: 1;}
div {
	background: red;
	border: 1px solid white;
	width: 20em;

	display: flex;
	flex-direction: column;
}
p {
	background: white;
	margin: 0;
	height: 2em;

	flex: 1;
}
@media projection, print {
	p {
		break-after: always;
	}
}
</style>

</head><body><h4>There should not be any red anytime. Enter fullscreen or print
	preview. You should not see the word fail on the first page
	after doing that.</h4>

<div>
	<p></p>
</div>
<h1>fail</h1>
</body></html>